==Korean==
===Verb===
'''잡다''' (''jabda, japda'')
# To [[take]], [[hold]], [[seize]], [[arrest]], [[catch]], [[capture]] cf. Latin [[captare]] "to [[chase]]", frequentative of [[capere]] "to [[take]]"
# To [[occupy]], [[take up]]
# To [[manage]], [[arrange]], [[reserve]], [[settle]]
# To [[butcher]], [[kill]] (''an animal'')
# To [[extinguish]]

====Synonyms====
*[[붙잡다]] (''butjabda, butjapda'') To [[catch]], [[capture]], [[seize]], [[arrest]], [[hold]], [[take]]
*[[붙들다]] (''butdeulda'') To [[catch]], [[capture]], [[seize]], [[arrest]], [[hold]], [[take]]

====Antonyms====
*[[놓치다]] (''nohchida'') To fail to [[catch]] or [[hold on]], [[miss]], [[let go]]

